## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests, 0 meaningful verifications.** This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class — every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called to inflate coverage metrics, but almost nothing is actually verified. Bugs in price calculation, CSV parsing, search logic, and deletion would all pass these tests silently.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 7 |
| High | 0 |
| Medium | 2 |
| Low | 1 |

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic — entire class)

The class methodically calls every method on `ProductCatalog` with no or trivial assertions. This is **the** reason bugs escape to production despite 95% coverage.

**Tests with zero assertions** (lines 17–21, 33–36, 39–42, 63–66, 69–74, 85–88):

| Test | Calls | Asserts |
|------|-------|---------|
| `AddProduct_Works` | `AddProduct` | ❌ Nothing |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | `UpdatePrice` | ❌ Nothing — never checks the new price |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | `RemoveProduct` | ❌ Nothing — never confirms item is gone |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | `GetProductCount` | ❌ Nothing — discards the count |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | `ApplyBulkDiscount` | ❌ Nothing — never checks discounted prices |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | `ImportFromCsv` | ❌ Nothing — never checks products were created |

**Tests with only `Assert.IsNotNull`** (lines 25–29, 47–52, 55–59, 77–82):

| Test | What's Missing |
|------|----------------|
| `GetProduct_Works` | Never checks SKU, Name, or Price of the returned product |
| `SearchProducts_Works` | Never checks result count or content — an empty list passes |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` | Same — empty list passes |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` | Never checks CSV content — `""` would pass |

**Concrete fix examples:**

```csharp
// BEFORE — UpdatePrice_Works (line 33)
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
}

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_UpdatesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}
